AFTA¿s flagship program is Art For The Animals¿, a unique education and development program that uses hand crafted folk artas thank you gifts for donors who contribute to participating wildlife organizations.  The art is crafted by local artisans who share the land or the region with the animals, and who are part of a conservation enterprise or economic self-sufficiency program, or an indigenous group trying to preserve its culture.  Art For The Animals: educates consumers and raises awareness of endangered species, environmental and sustainable development issues;  
raises funds for wildlife and nature conservancy;
creates a unique, self-fulfilling, culturally sensitive and potentially broad market for indigenous art and conservation enterprise products by offering specific pieces as donor premiums; changes consumer behavior ¿ turning excess holiday consumerism into conservationism and support for ecologically sustainable economic systems.

AFTA markets the program through its catalog, website and recently established Carmel shop.
